               Some departmental urgent engagements, dear Mr Clarke, prevent me from attending the meeting of the technolog. Committee this day;

Clarke had notified M of the meeting in a private note the day before (note not found; see n. 1 to M to M. Clarke, 14 November 1870).
                but if not unforeseen hindrances arise I hope to have the honor of being present next Tuesday.
